Operates on strings or character values

1. initcap

It converts first letter of string to capital letter.
Example: Select initcap('computer science') from dual;
O/P : Computer Science

2. Concatenate

It appends two or more literal expression,column values or variables into one string
Example: Select concat ('computer', 'science') from dual;

3. Replace

It is used to replace old string from new string.
Example: Select replace ('black and Blue','Bl' ,'j') from char
O/P: Jack and Jues

4. Lower
It is used to convert the string to the lower case

5. Upper
It is used to convert the string to the upper case

6. Substring
It is used to extract the portion of the string
Example: Select substr (Computer Science , 5, 4 )from dual;
O/P: uter


7. Translate
Select translate ('Jack', 'J' ,'P') from dual;
O/P: Pack

8. LTrim
Used to Trim left side characters
Example: Select ltrim ('Computer Science' , 'Comp') from dual;
O/P : uter Science

9. RTrim
Used to trim right side characters
Select RTrim ('Computer Science' , 'Science') from dual;
O/P: Computer

10. Soundex
It is a function which finds out the name which sounds like a given name with name present in table.
Select ename from emp where soundex (ename) = soundex('NILL');

11. Chr
This function gives the equivalent character value of provided number in the given function.

12. Lpad
This function pads the given symbol,given no.of times to the left side of the string,it takes three argument.

Original string, number, and character to be print.
Eg: Select lpad('DBMS' , 10, *) from dual;
O/p: ******DBMS

13. Rpad
Same as Lpad but functions from the right hand side

14. Length
It finds out the length of the given string
EG:Select length ('tech') from dual;
O/P: 4

15. Concatenate
It concatenates two or more string and displays the results.
Example: Select ename|| 'Is getting' || 'salary from emp where salary>50,000';
O/P: Ashna is getting 1,0000000;
